<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") %>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Privacy Policy | Wanderlust</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/style.css">
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: "Poppins", sans-serif;
      background: #f9f9f9;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 850px;
      margin: 50px auto;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 30px 35px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 3px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }
    h1 {
      color: #333;
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    h2 {
      color: #444;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      margin-top: 25px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    p, li {
      color: #555;
      line-height: 1.5;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
    }
    a {
      color: #007bff;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
    }
    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %></p>

    <p>
      Welcome to <strong>Wanderlust</strong>. We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. 
      This Privacy Policy explains how we collect and use your data when you interact with our platform.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      We collect only the information necessary to provide our services, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your name, username, and email address during registration.</li>
      <li>Details related to listings and reviews you create, such as titles, descriptions, and uploaded images.</li>
      <li>Location data associated with listings to display accurate map results.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To allow users to create, edit, and manage property listings.</li>
      <li>To show location-based maps for listings.</li>
      <li>To enable users to post and view reviews.</li>
      <li>To ensure secure authentication and account management.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      We use cookies to maintain login sessions and enhance your experience on Wanderlust. 
      You may disable cookies in your browser settings, though some site features may not function properly without them.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>
      We rely on a few trusted third-party services to make Wanderlust functional and efficient:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloudinary</strong> – securely stores and optimizes user-uploaded images in the cloud.</li>
      <li><strong>Mapbox</strong> – displays map data for listings to enhance discovery.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      These services follow their own privacy policies, which we encourage you to review.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Updates to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may occasionally revise this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices. 
      Updates will appear on this page along with the updated date shown above.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">About This Project</h2>
    <p>
      Wanderlust is a personal project created out of a passion for full-stack development and travel.  
      I've built this as part of my learning journey as a <b>4th-year Computer Science Engineering student.</b> 
      It combines design, code, and functionality to create a practical platform for sharing travel listings, reviews & making it
      engaging for users.
      I’m truly grateful that you’re taking the time to explore it.  
      <br><br>
      Feel free to connect or share your thoughts with me on 
      <a href="https://www.instagram.com/vish_chekkilla" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Instagram</a>.
    </p>

    <br>
    <p class="mt-4 text-center">
      <a href="/listings" class="text-decoration-none">&larr; Back to Exploring</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
